After my talk, we received feedback that the organisations represented in the audience had really engaged in a positive way with the content (both at the time and via feedback received following the day). This was followed up by in-person and email exchanges, especially for attendees from voluntary organisations linked to mental health/well-being (e.g., Rape Crisis, Headway). This bias in interest was, we suspect, due to our findings underscoring the positive benefits that can accrue from online forum involvement.

